## FAQ

**Q: What is the main difference between ChatGPT and Claude?**
A: ChatGPT is built by OpenAI and is known for its versatility, speed, and multi-modal features like web browsing and data analysis. Claude is built by Anthropic and focuses heavily on safety, natural writing style, and the ability to process massive amounts of text via a huge context window.

**Q: Can I use both ChatGPT and Claude for my business?**
A: Yes. Many businesses utilize both models for different tasks. Using a platform like Chatzy AI allows you to connect your own Claude or ChatGPT APIs and switch between them seamlessly without changing your core application infrastructure.

**Q: Is Claude better at writing than ChatGPT?**
A: In 2026, many writers and content creators prefer Claude for writing. It tends to produce more natural, human-sounding text and relies less on typical AI sentence structures compared to ChatGPT.

**Q: Which model is better for analyzing long documents?**
A: Claude is generally superior for massive document analysis. Its massive context window allows it to read hundreds of pages of text at once while maintaining near-perfect recall of the information.

**Q: Do both platforms offer enterprise security?**
A: Yes, both OpenAI and Anthropic offer robust security protocols for their enterprise tiers, ensuring your business data is not used to train future public AI models. 

